      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm seeing some weirdness in this c++ module. the memory usage just keeps climbing every time this loop runs. can u help me figure out why?\n\n```cpp\nvoid processTransactions(int count) {\n    for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {\n        double* transactionData = new double[100];\n        \n        // simulate some data processing\n        for(int j = 0; j < 100; ++j) {\n            transactionData[j] = static_cast<double>(i + j);\n        }\n\n        // logic to log or send data...\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
